parameters: ピクチャイベント登録

"There was a swarm of monsters on the mountain past this
cave. I was just on my way back from subduing them."

"More importantly, what about you, Suelle? Why are you in a
place like this?"
"I wanted some materials to make a new piece of equipment."

Suelle showed the ore he had been collecting until just a
moment ago.
"If you had told me, I would have come with you."

"Besides, this place was supposed to be relatively safe, so
I thought it would be no problem to come alone."

Tina also looked at the monsters she had defeated earlier
upon hearing Suelle's words.

"These monsters... they're not the kind that should be in a
place like this."

The monsters Tina had defeated were the kind that normally
required a party of several people to subdue. They were not
the type of monsters that should be near a town or in its
caves.
"Maybe there's been some disturbance in the ecosystem."

"But really, I owe you one. As expected of a member of
Lucent, the party that defeated the Demon Lord."

What Suelle said was true. Tina was indeed one of the
members who had defeated the Demon Lord.

However, Tina made a face that was hard to describe upon
hearing Suelle's words.

"You always talk as if it's someone else's business, but
weren't you also one of those members?"
Indeed, Suelle himself was also one of those heroic members.

Even so, Suelle himself doesn't have the same combat ability
as Tina.
"Even though I'm a member, I'm just an artificer."

Essentially, Suelle was quite poor at combat, and he joined
the party as an artificer to provide support for the hero's
party.

Artificers are items, weapons, and armor that utilize the
spells and techniques of this world. They usually come in
various forms and have a wide range of effects depending on
their purpose.
For example, Tina also has a ring made by Suelle.

This ring is a special piece of artifice that transforms
into a sword when Tina channels her power into it.

An artificer plays an important role in battle, developing,
adjusting, modifying, and repairing such artifice, and those
who perform these tasks are called artificers.

Therefore, even for a hero's party on a long journey, the
role of an artificer was essential.

"I was just providing support with the artifice. The ones
handling the combat were all Tina and the others."

Tina let out an even deeper sigh than before at Suelle's
words.

"The artifice you created has become the foundation for all
the artifice used in the world now."

"More importantly, as a matter of fact, it's dubious whether
we could have defeated the Demon Lord without your
artifice... I've said this many times."
"You seem to not quite understand that."

Tina understood what she wanted to say, but Suelle wasn't
being modest.

The way Tina and the others fought as a hero's party was so
impressive that Suelle had witnessed it up close.

"First of all, the ability to detect attacks from all
directions that Tina and the others do as if it's natural is
something that ordinary people absolutely can't do."

Of course, Suelle himself was included among those ordinary
people.

Having accompanied the hero's party, Suelle was often
exposed to situations where he didn't know when an attack
might come.

So, what should one do when surrounded by powerful
individuals who can detect attacks from all directions like
Tina?

The answer is simple. Stay still and rigid, trying not to
get in the way as much as possible.

This was understood to be the best course of action after
various experiences during the journey to defeat the Demon
Lord.

Perhaps because of this, no matter how useful the support is
said to be, it's always Tina and the others who actually
fight, and seeing this up close makes Suelle acutely aware
of his own lack of strength.

"Well, even if we can detect attacks from all directions, if
a clear non-combatant makes an unexpected surprise attack,
our reaction might be delayed."

"That's true, but Tina, you have a unique skill called Full
Body, right?"

In this world, people have unique skills that are different
from normal skills and are specific to individuals.
Full Body is one such skill, exclusive to Tina.

During the era of the Demon Lord's subjugation, there were
dangerous moments for Tina, such as when a child was
manipulated into making a surprise gunshot attack.

However, Tina's ability Full Body automatically deflects any
surprise attacks.

"Even so, Full Body only activates against surprise attacks
from those I don't recognize as enemies, and when it
switches to automatic defense, my consciousness is
interrupted for a moment."

"That momentary delay can become a critical vulnerability in
a battle against a formidable enemy, so I'd rather not
activate it too often."

The 'moment' Tina refers to is literally just an instant.
Suelle, with little experience in combat, couldn't even
perceive it.

"I feel like battles where such an instant can be decisive
won't happen anymore now that the Demon Lord is gone."

"Well, yes. But that doesn't mean we can neglect the fact
that there are still a large number of monsters in the
world, some of which are powerful."

"We can't afford to be careless and let our guard down. Now
that the hero has returned, I intend to continue my
training."

Tina is indeed one of the strongest in combat, just as
Suelle imagines.

But Suelle thought that Tina's true strength lay in her
continuous effort without becoming complacent.
"Oops, we've been talking for quite a while, haven't we?"

"Before any more monsters show up, let's head back to town
for now."

On the map, there are blue and red crystals. Approach them
and press the confirm key to activate their effects.

\C[1]Blue\C[0]   Fully restores allies' HP and MP.\C[2]
Red\C[0]   Transitions to reminiscence mode. Pubic hair
toggle.

Also, clicking on the speech bubble icon of a character
during map actions will give you hints about your next
objective.

If you're ever unsure about what to do next, please make use
of this feature.
